    "Model Choice": "A Physics-Informed Neural Network (PINN) utilizing Random Fourier Features (RFF) or Sine activation functions (SIREN). Standard MLPs suffer from spectral bias and fail to resolve the high-frequency components of steep gradients and shocks in the Burgers equation. Fourier feature mappings project the inputs into a higher-dimensional space, enabling the network to capture sharp spatial transitions on the periodic domain.",
    "Training Strategy": "Loss Function: Weighted sum of MSE for PDE residual, IC, and PBCs. Sampling: Sobol sequence for initial collocation points, augmented by Residual-Based Adaptive Refinement (RAR) to densely sample regions where the PDE residual is high (near shocks). Optimization: Adam optimizer for initial exploration, switching to L-BFGS for precise convergence. Loss Balancing: Use Neural Tangent Kernel (NTK) based adaptive weighting or SoftAdapt to dynamically balance the gradients of the IC, PBC, and PDE losses, preventing the network from ignoring the IC.",
